<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-12T09:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-12T09:49:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/53.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-12T10:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1915—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Haitian Senate ratified the treaty last night. The vote was, in favor
                            25, against 9, chairman of the Senate committee not voting. I am
                            informed by the Minister for Foreign Affairs that the Haitian Government
                            will submit for signature in a few days a modus vivendi embodying the
                            terms of the treaty and that the appointment of the commission to
                            proceed to Washington is now being considered.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>